John Charles, Makurdi Benue State Governor  Samuel Ortom    presented a budget of  N189.4bn  for 2020 to the House of  Assembly  for approval  on Tuesday. Ortom  also presented a  supplementary budget of N7,075,912,333. The  2020 budget is N10.3bn less than the 2019 budget of N199.7bn. The  governor christened  the 2020 budget  ‘Budget of Advancement, Growth and Development’. According to the  breakdown of the  budget, N115.5b  is earmarked for current expenditure, with personnel cost  to gulp  N50.6bn and  N63.9b  for overhead cost. The sum of  N74.9b was voted for capital projects. The governor  said  N73.7bn would  go to the economic sector while N64.6bn was budgeted for the social sector, with N48.2bn  for  the administrative sector. The justice sector has the lowest share of N2.8bn. The Speaker of the Assembly, Titus Uba, assured Ortom  that they  would ensure a  speedy passage of the budget. He said  the presentation of the 2020 budget  was the earliest budget proposal ever presented to the Assembly since  1999. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com   